## Account Rules

### Account kinds
The system must support at least:

- checking
- savings
- credit_card
- cash
- investment
- loan
- digital_wallet
- other

### On-budget vs tracking
The `is_on_budget` flag is important.

- on-budget accounts affect Ready to Assign
- tracking accounts do not affect Ready to Assign
- tracking accounts may still affect net worth

### Starting balances
Account starting balances may be represented as system-generated transactions.

The system must support opening balance behavior similar to:
- Starting Balance
- Inflow: Ready to Assign
- Category not needed

---

## Transaction Rules

### Transaction types
Transactions must support at least:

- income
- expense
- transfer
- adjustment
- bill_payment
- refund

### Transaction source
Transactions may be:
- manual
- imported
- synced
- system generated

### Splits
A single transaction may be split across multiple categories.

### Transfers
A transfer between two internal accounts must create paired transaction records linked by a transfer relationship.

Transfers must not be modeled as a single loose transaction without a clear source/destination relationship.

### Cleared status
Transactions may be cleared or uncleared.

### Credit card statements
Transactions may optionally belong to a credit card statement period.

---

## Recurring Rules

Recurring rules must support:

- recurring income
- recurring expense
- recurring transfer
- frequency
- interval
- next run date
- auto-create
- auto-post
- optional merchant/category/account references

Recurring rules may generate transactions, but transactions remain first-class persisted rows.

