## Database Change Rules

When changing the database schema:

- preserve `user_id` on protected tables
- preserve or update RLS policies
- preserve foreign keys and ownership consistency
- prefer additive migrations over destructive redesigns
- document behavior changes in this file
- update indexes if new high-volume query patterns are introduced

Do not make schema changes that simplify the schema at the expense of:
- security
- auditability
- budgeting behavior
- transfer correctness

---

## Guidance for Cursor / AI Agents

When generating code for this project:

- always assume the app is multi-tenant by user ownership
- always include user scoping in reads and writes
- never bypass RLS intentionally
- treat budget planning as a first-class domain, not only transactions
- do not collapse category groups and categories into a single table
- do not store money as float
- do not model transfers as unlinked loose records
- favor explicit relations and domain clarity over shortcuts

When uncertain, preserve:
- ownership
- auditability
- budgeting semantics
- month-based planning behavior
- future extensibility